eet - the Pork Store is incredible for breakfast and lunch. If there are no tables, hop on a seat at the counter. The pancakes are unbelievable. Walked from the corner of Ashbury down to Goldn Gate Park. I wish we had more time to spend there. Got to see a really neat drum circle. Ameoba records is pretty cool on the corner before the park. We also did the Alcatraz tour. That was really enjoyable. It's so interesting over there. The day we left, we rented a car from the Hertz down the block from the hotel. The woman who helped us was a little crazy, but she was nice enough to us. Gave us great directions out of the city to Route 1. We were heading to Big Sur for our wedding ceremony. What a lovely drive. Overall we had a great two days in San Francisco and a great stay at the Fisherman's Wharf Marriott.	
